In France at that time, every fourth imported station wagon was a Lada. Lada cars could be found in Asia, Africa, Latin America, Canada, Australia and Oceania. The front-wheel drive Lada cars of the Samara, Samara- 2, as well as models of the “tenth” family [47]. By 1990, 25% of the production of the car factory was exported, most of which was in Western Europe [48]. In 1995, an assembly kit center (CSK) was formed to further consolidate AvtoVAZ products, including in foreign markets.